===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|stan|lang=enm}}, {{term|ston|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|stan|stān|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|stainaz|lang=en}} (cf. Dutch {{term|steen|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Stein|lang=de}}), from {{proto|Indo-European|stāi-|lang=en}} (compare Latin {{term|stiria|lang=la}} ‘icicle’, Russian {{term|стена||wall|tr=stená|lang=ru|sc=Cyrl}}, Ancient Greek {{term|στῖον||pebble|tr=stîon|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}, {{term||stear}} ‘tallow’, Albanian {{term|shtëng||hardened or pressed matter|lang=sq}}, Sanskrit {{term||styāyate}} ‘it hardens’).

